09/05/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- On Thursday (8 May) in Athens, the Military Committee for the EU wrapped up a meeting which focused on future prospects for the EU's Common Foreign and Security Policy.
Greek Defence Chief Gen Georgios Antonakopoulos briefed participants about progress made during the period Greece has held the EU's rotating presidency.
He reviewed the EU's military capacity, ability for rapid response, ability to apply space programmes in military operations, and common European military training.
(MPA - 08/05/03)
